# pip-audit waiver ledger — Dependency CVE Scan (security-scan.yml)
#
# WAIVER PROCESS
# ==============
# The "Dependency CVE Scan (pip-audit)" CI job fails on any known
# vulnerability in requirements.txt / requirements-dev.txt that is NOT
# listed in this file. To accept a finding as known risk:
#
#   1. Add the vulnerability ID (PYSEC-* / GHSA-* / CVE-*, exactly as
#      pip-audit prints it) on its own line below.
#   2. Directly above the ID, add a comment block with:
#      - package==version affected, fix version
#      - WHY the risk is accepted (exposure analysis, not "busy")
#      - a removal condition (usually "remove when <pkg> bumped to <ver>")
#   3. Waivers are reviewed in the PR that adds them — an entry without a
#      justification comment should be rejected in review.
#
# Each line below is passed to pip-audit as --ignore-vuln <ID>.
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
#
# PREFERRED RESOLUTION is always bumping the pin in requirements*.in and
# re-running pip-compile — a waiver is a loan, not a payment.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ACTIVE WAIVERS (added 2026-06-10, PR "ci: dependency CVE scan gate")
# These 8 findings pre-date the gate. Waived to land the gate without
# coupling it to runtime dependency bumps (Class A CI-only change);
# follow-up dep-bump PR tracked in the gate PR body. Remove each entry
# when its package is bumped to the fix version.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# idna 3.13 → fix 3.15 (also appears via requirements-dev.txt).
# CVE-2026-45409: quadratic-time processing of crafted labels in
# encode/uts46 contexto checks (DoS via CPU burn). Graider calls idna only
# transitively via requests/httpx on outbound URLs we construct or receive
# from authenticated SIS/LMS configs — not on bulk anonymous input.
# Remove when: idna >= 3.15 in requirements.txt.
GHSA-65pc-fj4g-8rjx

# mako 1.3.11 → fix 1.3.12.
# CVE-2026-44307: Windows-only backslash path traversal in TemplateLookup.
# Graider deploys on Linux (Railway / ubuntu CI) and mako is a transitive
# dep of alembic (migration tooling), never user-facing TemplateLookup.
# Remove when: mako >= 1.3.12 in requirements.txt.
GHSA-2h4p-vjrc-8xpq

# pyjwt 2.12.1 → fix 2.13.0 — FOUR advisories. HIGHEST-PRIORITY follow-up:
# pyjwt verifies ClassLink OIDC id_tokens and Supabase JWTs here.
# - PYSEC-2026-179 / CVE-2026-48526: JWK-as-HMAC-secret key confusion when a
#   verifier accepts both asymmetric and HMAC algorithms. Graider's decode
#   call sites each pin ONE algorithm: auth.py `validate_token` (ES256
#   JWKS attempt and separate HS256 legacy-secret fallback, each a
#   single-algorithm decode), lti.py `validate_launch_jwt` (RS256),
#   classlink_routes.py `classlink_callback` (RS256). The mixed-algorithms
#   precondition is not met — re-verify if any decode call site changes
#   its algorithms= list.
PYSEC-2026-179
# - PYSEC-2026-175 / CVE-2026-48522: PyJWKClient passes uri to urlopen with
#   file:// / ftp:// / data:// handlers enabled. Our JWKS URLs are
#   https:// constants from trusted IdP config, not user input.
PYSEC-2026-175
# - PYSEC-2026-177 / CVE-2026-48524: unknown-kid JWKS refetch with no rate
#   limit (outbound request amplification). Bounded here by flask-limiter
#   on the SSO endpoints that trigger verification.
PYSEC-2026-177
# - PYSEC-2026-178 / CVE-2026-48525: detached-JWS b64=false handling.
#   Graider never uses unencoded-payload (RFC 7797) tokens.
PYSEC-2026-178
# Remove all four when: pyjwt >= 2.13.0 in requirements.txt.

